    text: "If, from the day the valuation under Article 51 of this Law was carried out until the moment the non-cash contribution is brought into the company, circumstances arise that reduce the value of that non-cash contribution, the company must, before that contribution is brought in, perform a new valuation in accordance with Articles 51 to 53 of this Law.\n\nIn the case referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article, the member making the non-cash contribution must pay the company the difference in value in money within the period for making the non-cash contribution.",
