    text: "A company may be divided by simultaneously transferring all assets and liabilities to:\n\n1) two or more newly incorporated companies (hereinafter: division by incorporation), or\n\n2) two or more existing companies (hereinafter: division by merger), or\n\n3) one or more newly incorporated companies and one or more existing companies (hereinafter: mixed division).\n\nThe company referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article ceases to exist after the transformation is carried out, without liquidation proceedings.",
